<br>
Say everyone wants ol' Vince to be GL, everyone declares fealty to Vincent.<br>
<br>
After a while, Vincent's drunken carousing and repeated thumping things with amusing carved sayings on his staff gets on some people's nerves and they want Rasha to be GL, they declare their fealty to Rasha.<br>
<br>
But Rasha only has 45% of the guild declaring fealty to him so he's just ol' Rasha and Vincent's patented &quot;nights of liver destruction&quot; continue as he practices Friar Stealth in the local wine cellars.<br>
<br>
Finally, when a few others have had enough, and declare their fealty to Rasha or someone else and someone gets the majority, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>They</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> become the GL and Vincent gets demoted and sent to rehab for a few decades.<br>
<br>
Basically this gets away from the &quot;guild leader owns the guild&quot; to &quot;the members who make up the guild, own it&quot; which is how *I* believe it should be -- after all, the members make the reputation of the guild, why should they have to start over just to depose one power-hungry friar? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.silverdaggers.net"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.silverdaggers.net/sigs/vincent1a.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/bdaggersincamelot.showUserPublicProfile?gid=norwoodblack>Norwood Black</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 613<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(6/10/03 12:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1668.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Horizons Beta</span><hr size=1> A site I did not know about until tonight.  Some good beta info.<br>
